long_desc.thetext:
Currently there is a convention to name variables which in fact accept multiple arguments are written like this:

@param varargs {String} Selector expression (or multiple ones)

It would be nicer to have a good name for the parameter instead which reflects the type of content which is accepted. I would suggest the following to make it possible to easily see which parameters are expanded this way:

@param selector {String...} Selector expression

The three "ellipsis" dots can then be parsed and may be used to add a nice decription to the API viewer. I also think that this "..." is quite readable in the signature of each function. Much better than just a name like any other e.g. "varargs".
